Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 6:20 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of June 24, 2016, Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund has been acquired by Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund. Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched by Calvert Group, Ltd. The fund is managed by Calvert Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets across the globe. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in dividend paying value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations, with a focus on mid-cap and large-cap companies. The fund invests in the stocks of socially conscious companies which a...
As of June 24, 2016, Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund has been acquired by Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund. Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched by Calvert Group, Ltd. The fund is managed by Calvert Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets across the globe. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in dividend paying value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations, with a focus on mid-cap and large-cap companies. The fund invests in the stocks of socially conscious companies which are focused on environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria. It employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors like valuation and prospects, growth and earnings dynamics, earnings quality, free cash flows, market sentiment, use of capital, favorable supply/demand conditions for key products or businesses, competitive position in the marketplace, and quality of management to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Russell 1000 Value Index and Lipper Equity Income Funds Average. It conducts proprietary research to create its portfolio. The fund does not invest in the stocks of companies that demonstrate poor environmental performance or compliance records, contribute significantly to local or global environmental problems, or include risks related to the operation of nuclear power facilities, are the subjects of serious labor-related actions or penalties by regulatory agencies, exhibit a pattern and practice of human rights violations, exhibit a pattern and practice of violating the rights and protections of Indigenous Peoples, demonstrate poor corporate governance or engage in harmful or unethical business practices, manufacture tobacco products, have significant and direct involvement in the manufacture of alcoholic beverages or gambling operations, manufacture or sell firearms and/or ammunition, abuse animals, develop genetically-modified organisms for environmental release without countervailing social benefits. It was formerly known as Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Equity Income Fund. Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Equity Income Fund was formed on October 31, 2011 is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


4550 Montgomery AvenueSuite 1000NBethesda, MD 20814United StatesFounded in 2011



Phone: 301-951-4881

Fax: 301-657-7014








