Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 6:20 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of June 24, 2016, Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund has been acquired by Calvert Social Investment Fund - Calvert Equity Portfolio. Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched by Calvert Group, Ltd. The fund is managed by Calvert Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets across the globe. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations, with a focus on mid-cap and large-cap companies. The fund invests in the stocks of socially conscious companies which are focused on environmental, socia...
As of June 24, 2016, Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund has been acquired by Calvert Social Investment Fund - Calvert Equity Portfolio. Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched by Calvert Group, Ltd. The fund is managed by Calvert Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets across the globe. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations, with a focus on mid-cap and large-cap companies. The fund invests in the stocks of socially conscious companies which are focused on environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria. It employs fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors such as current financial condition and industry position, market, economic, political, and regulatory conditions, earnings, assets, cash flows, allocation of capital, favorable supply/demand conditions for key products, development of new products or businesses, competitive position in the marketplace, quality of management, and companies and other enterprises that demonstrate varying degrees of commitment and progress toward addressing key corporate responsibility and sustainability challenges to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Russell 1000 Value Index and Lipper Large-Cap Value Funds Average. It conducts proprietary research to create its portfolio. The fund does not invest in the stocks of companies that demonstrate poor environmental performance or compliance records, contribute significantly to local or global environmental problems, or include risks related to the operation of nuclear power facilities, are the subjects of serious labor-related actions or penalties by regulatory agencies, exhibit a pattern and practice of human rights violations, exhibit a pattern and practice of violating the rights and protections of indigenous peoples, demonstrate poor corporate governance or engage in harmful or unethical business practices, manufacture tobacco products, have significant and direct involvement in the manufacture of alcoholic beverages or gambling operations, manufacture or sell firearms and/or ammunition, abuse animals,  and develop genetically-modified organisms for environmental release without countervailing social benefits. It was formerly known as Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Large Cap Value Fund. Calvert SAGE Fund - Calvert Global Value Fund was formed on December 29, 1999 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


4550 Montgomery AvenueSuite 1000NBethesda, MD 20814United StatesFounded in 1999



Phone: 301-951-4881

Fax: 301-657-7014








